    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Minister in Paris to the Minister of Foreign
                        Affairs.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received the note which your excellency
                    wrote to me on the 7th ultimo in answer to a communication I had the honor to
                    address you on the 1st of said month, with respect to the alleged projects of
                    Dr. Gwin and his associates in Mexico.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to transmit to your excellency the enclosed copy of a despatch
                    which I have just received from my government.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this occasion, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN BIGELOW.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>For enclosure see Mr. Seward’s despatch to Mr. Bigelow, No. 231, August 24,
                        1865, page—.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
